CYPRUS: British tourist drowns off Cyprus coast.British tourist drowns off Cyprus coast.A British tourist drowned off the coast of Cyprus on Tuesday while swimming with his wife and daughter, police in the resort town of Paphos said.Robert Michail Mcguire, 47, from London, was staying with his family at Venus Hotel in the west coast town of Paphos.A police officer said the sea was rough when the family went for an evening swim."When people see large waves they don't think of their safety they're just concerned with enjoying themselves," the police officer said.